== Modes I use ==

There are a couple of modes and packages I constantly use on my Zaurus with Emacs:

* PythonMode - 'cause I'm a Python programmer; now I use python.el (python-21.el)  instead of simple python-mode.el. With python mode I use [http://www.loveshack.ukfsn.org/emacs/pair-mode.el pair-mode] and ElDoc.
* EmacsWikiMode with PlannerMode and RememberMode (now I'm trying EmacsMuse).
* EmacsMuse as WYSIWYM for blogs and pages at WordPress.com
* JabberEl and EmacsIRCClient to communicate with people
* WikipediaMode which I use to edit MetaWiki pages (such as http://www.zaurus.ru/wiki/)
* WikitextMode which I made from WikipediaMode to use it editing my articles on [http://www.wikispaces.com/ Wikispaces] (see [http://www.wikispaces.com/wikitext wikitext markup rules])
* SimpleWikiEditMode which I slightly modified (support for TWiki markup rules, MediaWiki syntax improved a bit...)
* BalanceMode (a bit hacked by myself) - I use it to keep track of my bank account 
* GoMode - I like this game and often play against GNU Go
* WebloggerMode - 

All my version of the packages you can find here: [http://ru.oramezo.org/projects/emacs-packages].

